with alpha rewards you have 4 categories
- miners
- validators
- subnet owner
- nominators

miners are the ones doing the work. 41% of the rewards go to them.

18% goes to the subnet owner.

41% goes to the validators & nominators

the miners can take the tokens tied to their hotkey and move the stake to a validator hotkey. when they do this, they become a nominator (staker) in the process and begin earning emissions from that other 41%. so they are basically getting dual rewards

if you are a miner and have max conviction in the subnet, then you will want to do this. you earn the tokens from the work you do, and over time, as root proportion of the divs go down, you also begin earning more as a nominator. holding stake in your subnet keeps tao in the pool. and this keeps your subnet's price and emission rate high.

you want to keep your price high because this keeps the value of your daily rewards high, as well as the value of your stake that you are building as a nominator.

if you see miners doing this in a subnet you like, then it's a very good sign. because they are not dumping all the tokens that they earn, which would have their token price trend to zero. instead, they see the value in the subnet just like you as a nominator would.  

personally, I think it's good that the ones that do the work and have max conviction are the ones that are rewarded the most. 

repeat this across hundreds of subnets and you'll end up having really strong and robust communities that strive to drive more value to their subnet and subnet token long-term
